// @n8n-harness:primitive — exempt from pure-function discipline
//
// No-op stub. Orphaned locks self-heal via the client-side TTL check in
// lock_acquisition's parse_and_check_lock node: any new acquire on the same
// scope after locked_at + ttl_seconds will overwrite the stale value.
//
// Trade-off: between the failed execution and the next contention on the same
// scope, the lock key sits in Redis with stale ownership info. Worst case is
// `ttl_seconds` of unavailable lock + however long until the next caller tries
// to acquire. With the default 86400s (24h) ttl this can be unacceptable for
// hot scopes — override --ttl-seconds per-workflow when wrapping with
// add-lock-to-workflow.
//
// To upgrade this stub to active cleanup later, replace it with: GET the lock
// at the failed scope, JSON.parse the value, check if execution_id matches
// the failed execution ($workflow.errorData?.execution?.id), DEL if match.
// Requires scope-discovery: either iterate all `lock-*` keys in Redis (Redis
// node `keys` operation) or maintain a `lock-by-execution-${executionId}`
// owner pointer written at acquire time.
const executionId = $workflow.errorData?.execution?.id || $execution.id;
return [{
  json: {
    cleaned: false,
    reason: 'TTL-bounded cleanup — orphan locks self-heal via lock_acquisition stale-check',
    executionId,
  },
}];
